Cars.CarDescription: Old Rag Mountain Loop is a 9.5 mile heavily trafficked loop trail located near Etlan, Virginia that features a river and is rated as difficult. The trail is primarily used for hiking and is best used from May until October.

White Oak Canyon Trail is a 9.5 mile heavily trafficked out and back trail located near Syria, Virginia that features a waterfall and is rated as difficult. The trail offers a number of activity options and is best used from March until November. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.

Harpers Creek Shelter via Appalachian Trail is a 5.1 mile lightly trafficked out and back trail located near Tyro, Virginia that offers the chance to see wildlife. The trail is rated as difficult and is primarily used for hiking and running.
Cars.TrailAddress: Appalachian National Scenic Trail, Tyro, VA 22976
